{"id": "292289", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=292289", "title": "Zur'ak Firefist", "text": "Zur'ak Firefist is a &lt;a href=\"Jungle%20troll\"&gt;troll&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Earthen%20Ring\"&gt;Earthen Ring&lt;/a&gt; and a member of its &lt;a href=\"Elder%20Council\"&gt;Elder Council&lt;/a&gt;. He believed that the elements had abandoned the Earthen Ring. Zur'ak alongside &lt;a href=\"Kettara%20Bloodthirst\"&gt;Kettara Bloodthirst&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Krelna\"&gt;Krelna&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Lenka\"&gt;Lenka&lt;/a&gt;, were waiting for a meeting with &lt;a href=\"Drek%27Thar\"&gt;Drek'Thar&lt;/a&gt;. After the meeting, he alongside his master and colleagues noticed a fire in Camp Narache. He battled against the fire and centaur but the shaman were forced to retreat to Bloodhoof Village. There the shaman, especially Zur'ak, talked about how elements abandoned them. However a runner from Narache approached them, telling that the threat was over. Back in the camp, he witnessed Shotoa's power and chose to follow &lt;a href=\"Shotoa\"&gt;Shotoa&lt;/a&gt;'s teachings like many other members of the Earthen Ring. After Shotoa's betrayal he along with the other members of the Earthen Ring battled the elementals of Shotoa and his Grimtotem allies, and in the end they managed to defeat Shotoa."}
{"id": "363024", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=363024", "title": "Zur'chaka the Bonecrafter", "text": "Zur'chaka the Bonecrafter is a &lt;a href=\"Zandalari%20troll\"&gt;Zandalari troll&lt;/a&gt; located at the &lt;a href=\"Za%27Tual%20boneyard\"&gt;Za'Tual boneyard&lt;/a&gt; on the &lt;a href=\"Isle%20of%20Thunder\"&gt;Isle of Thunder&lt;/a&gt;.\nStrategy.\nBefore starting the encounter, try to clear some of the area around Zur'chaka, as movement is a big part of the fight. Kill a few &lt;a href=\"Zandalari%20Boneworker\"&gt;Zandalari Boneworker&lt;/a&gt;s and pull him closer to the &lt;a href=\"Eternal%20Spirit%20of%20Tharon%27ja\"&gt;Eternal Spirit of Tharon'ja&lt;/a&gt;, who does not play a part in the encounter.\nZur'chaka will start channeling Spirit Bolts, which should be interrupted, or they will hit for 16,500 Shadow every half-second. He will also summon a Fountain of Skulls, which launches missiles all over the area randomly for roughly 10 seconds. If a missile hits the ground within 2 yards of a player, it will inflict 50,000 Shadow damage.\nEvery 40 seconds after the start of the encounter, Zur'chaka will Roll the Bones. He will cast Strengthen Bones on himself (), increasing all damage output by 10% for the rest of the encounter, cast Mend Bones at all enemies within 20 yards of him (), healing them for ~200,000 health each, or cast Fountain of Skulls again (). Strengthen Bones does stack, and affects his melee swings, Spirit Bolts, and Fountain of Skulls.\nStart unloading on Zur'chaka right from the start, as his damage output will only go higher the longer the encounter lasts. Interrupt his Spirit Bolts, which will not be cast that frequently, and dodge the Fountain of Skulls while still trying to do damage to him. He will Roll the Bones every 40 seconds, so make sure to be within 20 yards of him in case he rolls Mend Bones for the free heal. Otherwise, make sure not to pull any additional mobs while moving about."}
{"id": "526697", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=526697", "title": "Zuraal the Ascended", "text": "Zuraal the Ascended is the first boss in the &lt;a href=\"Seat%20of%20the%20Triumvirate%20%28instance%29\"&gt;Seat of the Triumvirate&lt;/a&gt;. He has been mutated by the &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt; by the &lt;a href=\"ethereal\"&gt;ethereal&lt;/a&gt;s of the &lt;a href=\"Shadowguard\"&gt;Shadowguard&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nAdventure Guide.\n\"Zuraal represents the &lt;a href=\"Shadowguard\"&gt;Shadowguard&lt;/a&gt;'s first success at creating a &lt;a href=\"Void\"&gt;Void&lt;/a&gt;-infused &lt;a href=\"Broken\"&gt;Broken&lt;/a&gt; whose mind has not fallen into madness. A renowned brawler in his past life, Zuraal uses his newfound dark strength to empower his attacks and decimate his foes.\"\nOverview.\nZuraal uses the void to empower himself and injure his opponents. Decimate creates pools of damaging void energy, while Coalesced Void empowers all of Zuraal's abilities. Every once in awhile, Zuraal will cast Umbra Shift on a random target, sending them to the Void Realm. While the party member is in the Void Realm, Zuraal the Ascended will fixate on random targets and chase them down, casting Maddened Strike if he gets too close. The party member in the Void Realm can kill Dark Aberrations to gain void energy in order to cast Void Tear. Casting Void Tear stuns Zuraal and removes Maddened Frenzy, causing him to no longer fixate.\nSpeculation.\nAs he used to be a renowned brawler, Zuraal might have practiced &lt;a href=\"Jed%27hin\"&gt;Jed'hin&lt;/a&gt;."}
