{"id": "682998", "revid": "41171629", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=682998", "title": "Reckoning (disambiguation)", "text": "Reckoning may refer to:"}
{"id": "31479", "revid": "49723770", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=31479", "title": "Reckoning (paladin talent)", "text": "Reckoning is a &lt;a href=\"paladin\"&gt;paladin&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"talent\"&gt;talent&lt;/a&gt; in the Protection tree; you will need to spend 25 points in Protection to max it. This talent gives the paladin a chance to gain an additional attack on their next &lt;a href=\"auto-attack\"&gt;auto-attack&lt;/a&gt;, stacking up to 4 times.\nReckoning Bomb.\nThe term Reckoning Bomb refers to an attack that consumes multiple Reckoning \"charges\" at once, dealing a burst of damage via consecutive attacks. This is done by turning off &lt;a href=\"auto-attack\"&gt;auto-attack&lt;/a&gt; and allowing yourself to be critically hit until multiple stacks are accumulated, then turning it back on to use them all.\nReckoning could originally store an infinite number of charges, which meant Reckoning Bombs had the potential to deal massive amounts of damage. In May 2005, a paladin named Karmerr soloed &lt;a href=\"Lord%20Kazzak%20%28tactics%29\"&gt;Lord Kazzak&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Blasted%20Lands%20%28Classic%29\"&gt;Blasted Lands&lt;/a&gt; by unleashing a 1,816-charge Reckoning on him, killing him in a matter of seconds.\nShortly after this, Reckoning was hotfixed to store a maximum of only 4 charges."}
