{"id": "17635", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=17635", "title": "The Great Anvil", "text": "The Great Anvil is an &lt;a href=\"anvil\"&gt;anvil&lt;/a&gt; located in the center of the &lt;a href=\"Great%20Forge\"&gt;Great Forge&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Ironforge\"&gt;Ironforge&lt;/a&gt;. It has been in use for unknown centuries. Many weapons and objects of beauty have been crafted upon it, including the &lt;a href=\"Ashbringer\"&gt;Ashbringer&lt;/a&gt;, which was made by &lt;a href=\"Magni%20Bronzebeard\"&gt;King Magni Bronzebeard&lt;/a&gt; himself. When Magni became mobile again after being turned to diamond four years earlier, the Anvil was the first thing he went to see in his walkabout around the city.\nThe Great Anvil can be used both for &lt;a href=\"blacksmithing\"&gt;blacksmithing&lt;/a&gt; and as a &lt;a href=\"forge\"&gt;forge&lt;/a&gt; for smelting. No recipes are exclusive to it.\nSpeculation.\n&lt;a href=\"Ironforge%20-%20the%20Awakening%20of%20the%20Dwarves\"&gt;Ironforge - the Awakening of the Dwarves&lt;/a&gt; states: \"Constructing an altar for their &lt;a href=\"Khaz%27goroth\"&gt;Titan father&lt;/a&gt;, the dwarves crafted a mighty forge within the heart of the mountain.\" This religious altar and the Great Anvil are presumably one and the same."}
