ve of enemies at the base of the steps.\nClear out the other group on the other side of Athanos.\nTake out Athanos, the Overtuned Sparring Assistant back from the &lt;a href=\"Assessing%20Your%20Spirit\"&gt;Assessing Your Spirit&lt;/a&gt; quest early in the &lt;a href=\"Bastion%20storyline\"&gt;Bastion storyline&lt;/a&gt; to continue.\nStage 6: Follow the Path.\nAs Athanos fell, so did the Truthbringer. Head southwest through what is about to be a huge pack of enemies, but Xandria swoops in and takes them all out:\nTake a right and go down the steps to the west, then cut north to reach Thenios, who is blocking the more forsworn from approaching:\nOn the dais just up the steps is the Anima Gateway. As players approach, Adrestes flies in, obviously wounded:\nInteract with the gateway to continue.\nStage 7: In Darkness' Domain.\nEngage her:\nAt 60%, Lysonia goes immune and stuns the party before flying off.\nStage 8: A Clever Ploy.\nInteract with Chyrus to get a lift back to Elysian Hold:\nChyrus drops players off near where &lt;a href=\"Cassius\"&gt;Cassius&lt;/a&gt; is kneeling wounded, ending the stage. Above, kyrian fight the Forsworn, as do the Paragons in the remaining parts of Elysian Hold. Continue toward the Rise.\nFinal Stage: The Greater Good.\nLysonia, still at 60% health, is at Adrestes' usual position before the Archon's Rise, staring at Kyrestia the Firstborne. Run up the stairs to start the encounter:\nFinish her off:"}
