{"id": "131520", "revid": "26776761", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=131520", "title": "The Grind", "text": "The Grind is an award-winning comedy &lt;a href=\"machinima\"&gt;machinima&lt;/a&gt; series created by the filmmaking team &lt;a href=\"http%3A//www.oblivious-films.com/\"&gt;Oblivious Films&lt;/a&gt; and filmed on the server. The show revolves around some toons that blah blah Mac thought he'd put his buddies in a series of shows blah blah finish this Drewbie! \nHistory.\nMac thought he could make some movies so he did\u2026etc, etc.\nEpisodes.\nThis episode introduces some of the characters and was basically a testbed for the methods Mac would use in future episodes. This first episode introduces the characters of Deso, Macheath, and Drewbie, primarily; but features cameos from future stars Equoria, Sheil, Liuv, and Gnorlin as well.\nThe storyline of the series gets rolling. Our heroes find themselves on the losing end of a fight against the dragon Onyxia. Feeling utterly defeated, the group tries desperately to remember what they're supposed to be doing.\nPicking up where episode 1 left off, Deso has fallen off of Ironforge with a new friend, Liuv has somehow found himself naked in Orgrimmar, while Drewbie and Sheil try to get more info from Mac.\nDrewbie and Sheil tell the guildies to find a dwarf priest, while Deso observes the power of a girl character from Nynnja. The dwarf shadow priest, Tito, terrorizes Moonbrook, when Mac realizes he is a dwarf priest. Liuv, Gnorlin, and Equoria arrive back home, when Gnorlin finds his portal runes. A party occurs where Drewbie announces that they've found a dwarf priest. Everyone learns of the Burning Crusade expansion, and sets off for Outland, realizing that Wrath of the Lich King has come out already.\nRelated movies.\nThe Grind crew gets together to tell some ghost stories around the old campfire. All is going well til a scream rings out in the night.\nThe Grind crew reacts to Macheath's hideous new face. \nOther movies by Oblivious Films.\nAn easily frightened dwarf stumbles upon a strange machine in the middle of the road. Little does he know that this \"metal pig\" is about to take him and his friends on quite an adventure. From sexy dancing girls to deep dark dungeons (where a familiar man lurks), this Rumpus Machine has a mind of its own!\nCreated for and entered in the 2008 Blizzcon machinima contest, Mac convinced the voice actor for 'Deckard Cain', Michael Gough, to lend his voice to this movie as his well known Diablo character, although the name of the character was never mentioned in the film.\nA music video by Oblivious Films set to the song \"Super Bon Bon\" by Soul Coughing. Just a fun little thing they did before they started making \"The Grind.\"\nCast and crew.\nThe show is written, directed and edited by &lt;a href=\"Macheath\"&gt;Macheath&lt;/a&gt;.\nEveryone in the cast performs the voice of their own Warcraft character. "}
