{"id": "247289", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=247289", "title": "The Halls Of Reflection (Alliance)", "text": "This quest is part of the quest chain.\nObjectives.\nBring your &lt;a href=\"Tempered%20Quel%27Delar\"&gt;Tempered Quel'Delar&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Sword%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Sword's Rest&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Reflection\"&gt;Halls of Reflection&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nYou have reforged and tempered the sword, yet it sits quietly in its sheath, showing no signs of the power it should possess. You say the sword pulls you, as though it possesses a will?\nDare you bring it where it wishes to go? It is not right that the sword should be this silent and this insistent, yet I fear that if you do not take the sword to its destination, we will never learn why. Take it into &lt;a href=\"Icecrown%20Citadel\"&gt;Icecrown Citadel&lt;/a&gt;'s Halls of Reflection, but be on your guard! I'll be waiting for you in &lt;a href=\"Frozen%20Halls\"&gt;The Frozen Halls&lt;/a&gt;\nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nWhat happened inside the Halls of Reflection?\nCompletion.\nI had not thought it possible for evil to take hold in such a sword, but I suppose it was naive of me. If the greatest of dragonkind's creations could be corrupted and turned against them, why not a mere sword?\nUther's advice is wise, &lt;name&gt;, and I would urge you to heed it quickly.\nNotes.\nAfter accepting the quest, players are debuffed with Quel'Delar's Compulsion: \"Quel'Delar pulses with darkness and seems to be pulling you toward the Halls of Reflection in Icecrown Citadel.\" This debuff does not confer any in-game effects besides pointing players to the next step of the quest.\nUpon entering &lt;a href=\"Sword%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Sword's Rest&lt;/a&gt; in the Halls of Reflection and approaching &lt;a href=\"Frostmourne\"&gt;Frostmourne&lt;/a&gt; while under Quel'Delar's Compulsion:\nQuel'Delar will spawn and attack the party, and must be \"killed\" in order to obtain the Subdued Quel'Delar. , who stands next to the pedestal of Frostmourne, instructs the player that they must take the sword to the &lt;a href=\"Sunwell\"&gt;Sunwell&lt;/a&gt; to cleanse it of its evil.\nAfter defeating the sword:\nTurn around, walk out of the dungeon, and go turn in the quest to pick up the next.\nIf you find the sword overpowering, you can abandon the quest and pick it up again at the quest giver outside of the 5 man Icc dungeons."}
{"id": "247339", "revid": "38791128", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=247339", "title": "The Halls Of Reflection (Horde)", "text": "This quest is part of the quest chain.\nObjectives.\nBring &lt;a href=\"Quel%27Delar\"&gt;Quel'Delar&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Sword%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Sword's Rest&lt;/a&gt; inside the &lt;a href=\"Halls%20of%20Reflection\"&gt;Halls of Reflection&lt;/a&gt;. Return to &lt;a href=\"Myralion%20Sunblaze\"&gt;Myralion Sunblaze&lt;/a&gt; at &lt;a href=\"Quel%27Delar%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Quel'Delar's rest&lt;/a&gt; after you have completed your journey.\nDescription.\nYou have re-forged and tempered the sword, yet it sits quietly in its sheath, little different from a mundane blade. You say the sword pulls you, as though it possesses a will?\nDare you bring it where it wishes to go? It is not right that the sword should be this silent and this insistent, yet I fear that if you do not take the sword to its destination, we will never learn why. Bear it with you to the Halls of Reflection, but be on your guard and prepare to tell me all of what you learn there. \nRewards.\nYou will receive: \nProgress.\nWhat happened inside the Halls of Reflection?\nCompletion.\nHow can evil take root in such a sword? I would not have thought it possible if the evidence wasn't here before my eyes. If the greatest of dragonkind's creations could be corrupted and turned against them, why not a mere sword?\nI believe Uther is right. You must heed his advice quickly, &lt;name&gt;.\nNotes.\nAfter accepting the quest, players are debuffed with : \"Quel'Delar pulses with darkness and seems to be pulling you toward the Halls of Reflection in Icecrown Citadel.\" This debuff does not confer any in-game effects besides pointing players to the next step of the quest.\nUpon entering &lt;a href=\"Sword%27s%20Rest\"&gt;Sword's Rest&lt;/a&gt; in the Halls of Reflection and approaching &lt;a href=\"Frostmourne\"&gt;Frostmourne&lt;/a&gt; while under Quel'Delar's Compulsion:\nQuel'Delar will spawn and attack the party, and must be \"killed\" in order to obtain the Subdued Quel'Delar. , who stands next to the pedestal of Frostmourne, instructs the player that they must take the sword to the &lt;a href=\"Sunwell\"&gt;Sunwell&lt;/a&gt; to cleanse it of its evil.\nAfter defeating the sword:\nTurn around, walk out of the dungeon, and go turn in the quest to pick up the next.\nIf you find the sword overpowering, you can abandon the quest and pick it up again at the quest giver outside of the 5 man Icc dungeons."}
