{"id": "320121", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=320121", "title": "The Harder They Fall", "text": "Objectives.\nKill 3 Molten Behemoths.\nDescription.\nMolten Behemoths have joined the elementals upon the battlefield. They are crushing our front lines. I need you to halt their momentum.\nYou'll find the beasts slow and clumsy. They can easily be outmaneuvered, but they will pack a devastating punch if they hit you. Be nimble, &lt;class&gt;.\nRewards.\nYou will receive: &lt;a href=\"Mark%20of%20the%20World%20Tree\"&gt;Mark of the World Tree&lt;/a&gt; x2 and \nProgress.\nEven with such monstrous opponents marching upon them, not a single one of my men has quit the field. &lt;a href=\"Jarod%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Jarod&lt;/a&gt; is to be commended. He inspires the men like no other.\nCompletion.\nThe elementals shall grow to fear you.\nNotes.\nMolten Behemoths are level 85 elite molten giants with 309,000 health and two abilities outside of basic melee:\nIt is possible to earn the achievement &lt;a href=\"Flawless%20Victory\"&gt;Flawless Victory&lt;/a&gt; by kiting a behemoth and solo-killing it without taking any damage from Molten Stomp or Fiery Boulder. As these mobs are designed to be kited, any class with a repeatable ranged attack (which is \"every\" class) can do this. Keep moving, especially when it winds up a fiery boulder. The casting time of Molten Stomp allows a melee attacker to get out of range before it goes off. Classes with only weak ranged abilities can repeatedly dodge out of melee range to avoid the stomp then back in to land another melee attack."}
