{"id": "501382", "revid": "49740203", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=501382", "title": "March of the Tadpoles", "text": "The \"March of the Tadpoles\" is an event in which the tadpole travel along side the &lt;a href=\"Westrift\"&gt;Westrift&lt;/a&gt;. Since it is dangerous, King Mrgl-Mrgl decides to interfere and makes adventurers their guardians. \nEvent.\nToday, the baby Winterfin murlocs of Borean Tundra complete their trip across the &lt;a href=\"Westrift\"&gt;Westrift&lt;/a&gt;.\nGetting Started.\nGo to &lt;a href=\"Winterfin%20Retreat\"&gt;Winterfin Retreat&lt;/a&gt; and talk to &lt;a href=\"King%20Mrgl-Mrgl\"&gt;King Mrgl-Mrgl&lt;/a&gt;. The king will allow to adopt one of tadpoles. With your tadpoles you will go to the bottom of the sea and collect &lt;a href=\"Winterfin%20Clam\"&gt;Winterfin Clam&lt;/a&gt;s. After returning to the surface, you help your murloc fight his fears by slaying the orca &lt;a href=\"Mrrga\"&gt;Mrrga&lt;/a&gt;. Greatful for all that you've done, the tadpole hands you a &lt;a href=\"Tadpole%20Gift\"&gt;gift&lt;/a&gt;."}
