{"id": "211556", "revid": "41554525", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=211556", "title": "Margoz (Cycle of Hatred)", "text": ""}
{"id": "114862", "revid": "39299307", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=114862", "title": "Margoz (human)", "text": "Margoz was a &lt;a href=\"fisherman\"&gt;fisherman&lt;/a&gt; native to &lt;a href=\"Kul%20Tiras\"&gt;Kul Tiras&lt;/a&gt; who had come to &lt;a href=\"Theramore\"&gt;Theramore&lt;/a&gt; soon after the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20of%20Mount%20Hyjal\"&gt;Battle of Mount Hyjal&lt;/a&gt; in an attempt to make more profit than he had in Kul Tiras. Still, according to his fellow fishermen, he was very unskilled and because he was small and weak, continued to live a very poor life and was often taken advantage of. He was eventually recruited into the service of a demon named &lt;a href=\"Zmodlor\"&gt;Zmodlor&lt;/a&gt;, who had established the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Blade%20clan\"&gt;Burning Blade&lt;/a&gt; cult among both the orcs and humans of Kalimdor. The cult's goal was to start a full-scale war between orcs and humans again and Margoz's job was to sow anti-orc sentiments in Theramore. His attempts to do so in the &lt;a href=\"Demonsbane%20Inn%20and%20Tavern\"&gt;Demonsbane&lt;/a&gt; tavern were very successful and Zmodlor continued to manipulate both the orcs and humans into starting another war between the Alliance and the Horde again.\n&lt;a href=\"Strov\"&gt;Strov&lt;/a&gt; was to find some information about the clan. His brother, &lt;a href=\"Manuel\"&gt;Manuel&lt;/a&gt;, showed him which person Margoz was. By that time, Margoz was drunk and left the tavern. Strov followed him and discovered that Margoz is in contact with a demon. Strov was ultimately killed by the demon Zmodlor who noticed that Strov was spying on Margoz.\nThe demon's plans were eventually discovered, and he was banished into the &lt;a href=\"Twisting%20Nether\"&gt;Twisting Nether&lt;/a&gt;. Margoz's fate after that is unknown."}
{"id": "22971", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22971", "title": "Margoz (orc)", "text": "Margoz is an &lt;a href=\"orc\"&gt;orc&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"quest%20giver\"&gt;quest giver&lt;/a&gt; located in a tent south of &lt;a href=\"Bladefist%20Bay\"&gt;Bladefist Bay&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Durotar\"&gt;Durotar&lt;/a&gt;."}
{"id": "22899", "revid": "22514", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=22899", "title": "Margoz (quest)", "text": "Objectives.\nSpeak with &lt;a href=\"Margoz\"&gt;Margoz&lt;/a&gt;.\nDescription.\nOne of our more useful &lt;a href=\"shaman\"&gt;shaman&lt;/a&gt;, Margoz, knows more of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Blade\"&gt;Burning Blade&lt;/a&gt;'s corruption. He speaks of a cave called &lt;a href=\"Skull%20Rock\"&gt;Skull Rock&lt;/a&gt; in the mountains, just outside &lt;a href=\"Orgrimmar\"&gt;Orgrimmar&lt;/a&gt;, that shelters a large band of Burning Blade cultists.\nBefore you go to Skull Rock, speak with Margoz. He is wise and his council is valued.\nHe is camped to the southeast, between the coast and &lt;a href=\"Drygulch%20Ravine\"&gt;Drygulch Ravine&lt;/a&gt;.\nFollow his advice, but whatever Margoz says, &lt;name&gt;, I still want you to crush those cultists! \nCompletion.\nWelcome, &lt;name&gt;. Word reached me of your coming, and of your exploits in &lt;a href=\"Durotar\"&gt;Durotar&lt;/a&gt;.\nYou are a &lt;class&gt; of growing skill and renown.\nStay on the pure path, and your future will be great indeed.\nNotes.\nMargoz stands at a small Horde encampment east of the &lt;a href=\"The%20Dranosh%27ar%20Blockade\"&gt;The Dranosh'ar Blockade&lt;/a&gt;.\nA short optional quest chain can be started by speaking to &lt;a href=\"Vek%27nag\"&gt;Vek'nag&lt;/a&gt;, who is pacing next to Margoz's camp. He starts &lt;a href=\"Sent%20for%20Help\"&gt;Sent for Help&lt;/a&gt;."}
