{"id": "566018", "revid": "42014766", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=566018", "title": "Marie Davenport", "text": "Marie Davenport is a &lt;a href=\"human\"&gt;human&lt;/a&gt; located in the &lt;a href=\"Davenport%20Residence\"&gt;Davenport Residence&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Millstone%20Hamlet\"&gt;Millstone Hamlet&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Stormsong%20Valley\"&gt;Stormsong Valley&lt;/a&gt;. She will offer 5 &lt;a href=\"Marie%27s%20Famous%20Cookies\"&gt;Marie's Famous Cookies&lt;/a&gt; per 20 &lt;a href=\"Tigule%27s%20Strawberry%20Ice%20Cream\"&gt;Tigule's Strawberry Ice Cream&lt;/a&gt; after her quests have been completed.\nIn her own days, she was quite the firecracker in her day. At some point, she tried to teach her grandson, &lt;a href=\"Charles%20Davenport\"&gt;Charles&lt;/a&gt; how to bake, but the effort was seemingly unfortunate since &lt;a href=\"Sergeant%20Calvin\"&gt;Sergeant Calvin&lt;/a&gt; remembers Its smoke.\nBy the time the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Alliance emissary&lt;/a&gt; delivered her lost &lt;a href=\"Marie%27s%20Package\"&gt;package of tea&lt;/a&gt;, she had the local residents running errands and collecting various supplies in order to put the hamlet back in order and save it from the ettins. This included Charles. With the collected flour and gunpoweder, she instructed the Alliance emissary to use &lt;a href=\"Flour%20Bomb\"&gt;flour bombs&lt;/a&gt; against the attacking ettins. Being thankful for helping her, she baked cookies for the adventurer and Charles.\nQuotes.\nGossip.\nWhy, hello there dear! Might you be able to help me with an errand or two? Only as long as it's no bother though!\nWe certainly do! Here, take a few of these flour bombs with you. Please, do be careful with them though.\nWell, I've been having a bit of a sweet tooth lately. I'd really love some delicious strawberry ice cream!\nI would be terribly grateful if you could find some for me. If it's not too much trouble, please bring enough to store for later. I hope I'm not being a bother!\nRelatives.\nShe may be related to &lt;a href=\"Noella%20Davenport\"&gt;Noella Davenport&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Amy%20Davenport\"&gt;Amy Davenport&lt;/a&gt;."}
