{"id": "323354", "revid": "41171629", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=323354", "title": "Marin Bladewing", "text": "Marin Bladewing is a &lt;a href=\"night%20elf\"&gt;night elf&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"warden\"&gt;warden&lt;/a&gt; serving under &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt;. She took part in the &lt;a href=\"Firelands%20Invasion\"&gt;Firelands Invasion&lt;/a&gt; as part of the &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Wardens\"&gt;Shadow Wardens&lt;/a&gt;, during which &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Hyjal\"&gt;Mount Hyjal&lt;/a&gt; was saved from the &lt;a href=\"elemental\"&gt;elemental&lt;/a&gt; forces of &lt;a href=\"Ragnaros\"&gt;Ragnaros&lt;/a&gt;. She later joined the &lt;a href=\"The%20Wardens\"&gt;Wardens&lt;/a&gt; in resisting the &lt;a href=\"Third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Azsuna\"&gt;Azsuna&lt;/a&gt;, under the command of &lt;a href=\"Sira%20Moonwarden\"&gt;Sira Moonwarden&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt;.\nAt the time of the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;, Marin and her fellow Wardens committed themselves to the &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; cause, and fought alongside their leader Maiev in &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Darkshore\"&gt;the campaign&lt;/a&gt; to drive the &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; from &lt;a href=\"Darkshore\"&gt;Darkshore&lt;/a&gt;.\nBackground.\nFirelands.\nMarin Bladewing originally appeared as a &lt;a href=\"Shadow%20Wardens\"&gt;Shadow Warden&lt;/a&gt; at the &lt;a href=\"Forlorn%20Spire\"&gt;Forlorn Spire&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"Molten%20Front\"&gt;Molten Front&lt;/a&gt;. There, she took part in the &lt;a href=\"Firelands%20Invasion\"&gt;campaign&lt;/a&gt; against the Fire Lord, &lt;a href=\"Ragnaros\"&gt;Ragnaros&lt;/a&gt;, and his minions, in order to save all of &lt;a href=\"Mount%20Hyjal\"&gt;Mount Hyjal&lt;/a&gt; from destruction. She was accompanied in this quest by a number of other Wardens.\nDraenor.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"War%20in%20Draenor\"&gt;War in Draenor&lt;/a&gt;, Marin was part of a contingent of &lt;a href=\"Warden\"&gt;Warden&lt;/a&gt;s sent by &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt; to protect &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Khadgar\"&gt;Archmage Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; as he worked against the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;a href=\"alternate%20Draenor\"&gt;alternate Draenor&lt;/a&gt;. Led by &lt;a href=\"Cordana%20Felsong\"&gt;Cordana Felsong&lt;/a&gt;, the group was stationed across the continent, with Marin herself being found in &lt;a href=\"Starfall%20Outpost\"&gt;Starfall Outpost&lt;/a&gt; in and &lt;a href=\"Yrel%27s%20Watch\"&gt;Yrel's Watch&lt;/a&gt; in .\nBroken Isles.\nBy the time of the &lt;a href=\"Third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion&lt;/a&gt; of the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, Marin and her &lt;a href=\"The%20Wardens\"&gt;fellow Wardens&lt;/a&gt; had reestablished themselves on the &lt;a href=\"Broken%20Isles\"&gt;Broken Isles&lt;/a&gt;, where they guarded the &lt;a href=\"Vault%20of%20the%20Wardens\"&gt;Vault of the Wardens&lt;/a&gt; against all threats. The &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;s' attack on the facility, aided by &lt;a href=\"Cordana%20Felsong\"&gt;Cordana Felsong&lt;/a&gt; herself, succeeded in breaching the Vault. Marin would act as &lt;a href=\"quartermaster\"&gt;quartermaster&lt;/a&gt; for the organization from &lt;a href=\"Wardens%27%20Redoubt\"&gt;Wardens' Redoubt&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Azsuna\"&gt;Azsuna&lt;/a&gt;, from which she and her sisters fought desperately to drive back the Legion's forces.\nBattle for Azeroth.\nWarden Bladewing and her sisters would answer the call of &lt;a href=\"Maiev%20Shadowsong\"&gt;Maiev Shadowsong&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Tyrande%20Whisperwind\"&gt;Tyrande Whisperwind&lt;/a&gt;, as the &lt;a href=\"kaldorei\"&gt;kaldorei&lt;/a&gt; prepared to retake &lt;a href=\"Darkshore\"&gt;Darkshore&lt;/a&gt; from its &lt;a href=\"Horde\"&gt;Horde&lt;/a&gt; occupiers during the &lt;a href=\"Fourth%20War\"&gt;Fourth War&lt;/a&gt;. They would venture with Maiev to &lt;a href=\"Bashal%27Aran\"&gt;Bashal'Aran&lt;/a&gt;, where they defended High Priestess Tyrande during her ritual to become the &lt;a href=\"Night%20Warrior\"&gt;Night Warrior&lt;/a&gt;, and subsequently witnessed her transformation.\nLater, Marin and her sisters took part in the &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Darkshore\"&gt;Battle for Darkshore&lt;/a&gt; alongside other &lt;a href=\"Alliance\"&gt;Alliance&lt;/a&gt; forces.\nQuotes.\nDo you have the courage to help us defeat the Legion?\n&lt;a href=\"Sira%20Moonwarden\"&gt;Another&lt;/a&gt; of our sisters has fallen to darkness. But that will not stop us from our duty."}
{"id": "67762", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=67762", "title": "Marin Noggenfogger", "text": "Marin Noggenfogger is the creator of the famous &lt;a href=\"Noggenfogger%20Elixir\"&gt;Noggenfogger Elixir&lt;/a&gt; and, ever since the &lt;a href=\"Cataclysm%20%28event%29\"&gt;Cataclysm&lt;/a&gt;, the baron of the &lt;a href=\"goblin\"&gt;goblin&lt;/a&gt; city of &lt;a href=\"Gadgetzan\"&gt;Gadgetzan&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Tanaris\"&gt;Tanaris&lt;/a&gt;. He is married to &lt;a href=\"Sprinkle%20Noggenfogger\"&gt;Sprinkle&lt;/a&gt;, whom he previously considered a mere friend. He is also a leader of the &lt;a href=\"Steamwheedle%20Cartel\"&gt;Steamwheedle Cartel&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion of the Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, he joined the &lt;a href=\"Uncrowned\"&gt;Uncrowned&lt;/a&gt; to give his expertise in poisons and alchemy.\nBiography.\nWorld of Warcraft.\nHaving heard of some strange creatures called &lt;a href=\"Thistleshrub%20Dew%20Collector\"&gt;dew collectors&lt;/a&gt; able to store water in special glands, Marin sent &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s to collect the glands. He tried it, and it tasted awful. Not wanting to give up on this, he had the adventurer ask &lt;a href=\"Sprinkle\"&gt;Sprinkle&lt;/a&gt; for help, which she provided in the form of a powder. When he mixed it with the dew, he created Noggenfogger Elixir and immediately saw profit in it.\nOnce, when Marin was running past some old troll ruins, he noticed a camp set up there. He didn't get to visit it as he was chased off by &lt;a href=\"vulture\"&gt;vulture&lt;/a&gt;s.\nCataclysm.\nHaving become baron of Gadgetzan, &lt;a href=\"Kelsey%20Steelspark\"&gt;Kelsey Steelspark&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Megs%20Dreadshredder\"&gt;Megs Dreadshredder&lt;/a&gt; tried to convince him to work with their factions. Their bickering resulted in Marin sending them to do some work instead, including dealing with the &lt;a href=\"Southsea%20Freebooters\"&gt;Southsea Freebooters&lt;/a&gt; in eastern Tanaris.\nHe also sent &lt;a href=\"Zeke%20Bootscuff\"&gt;Zeke Bootscuff&lt;/a&gt; to the &lt;a href=\"Gaping%20Chasm\"&gt;Gaping Chasm&lt;/a&gt; with a mission: Find out how to turn a profit on the &lt;a href=\"silithid\"&gt;silithid&lt;/a&gt;, or wipe them clean.\nLegion.\nMarin led the defense of Gadgetzan during the &lt;a href=\"Legion%20Invasion\"&gt;Legion Invasion&lt;/a&gt;s, driving a massive &lt;a href=\"shredder\"&gt;shredder&lt;/a&gt; with twin flamethrowers against the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt; attackers. After each invasion was successfully repelled, he offered \"slightly discounted Noggenfogger Elixirs all around!\"\nFollowing the tragic &lt;a href=\"Battle%20for%20Broken%20Shore\"&gt;Battle for Broken Shore&lt;/a&gt;, Marin revealed himself to be a part of the &lt;a href=\"Uncrowned\"&gt;Uncrowned&lt;/a&gt;. During the &lt;a href=\"class%20order\"&gt;class order&lt;/a&gt; campaign, he is found in the &lt;a href=\"Hall%20of%20Shadows\"&gt;Hall of Shadows&lt;/a&gt; managing the &lt;a href=\"Crucible%20of%20the%20Uncrowned\"&gt;Crucible of the Uncrowned&lt;/a&gt;. It appears Marin is the only person who truly knows how to work the venomous injections of the crucible into the &lt;a href=\"Adventurer\"&gt;Shadow's&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"artifact\"&gt;artifact&lt;/a&gt;s and is thus a very valuable asset, though he uses this position for his own gain.\nIn addition to aiding the Shadow on their quest to fight the Legion, Marin also asks for their help on a money-making venture: Stealing a powerful genuine love potion from the vault of &lt;a href=\"Jastor%20Gallywix\"&gt;Trade Prince Gallywix&lt;/a&gt;. Marin thanks the adventurer and serves them as a &lt;a href=\"champion\"&gt;champion&lt;/a&gt;.\nBattle for Azeroth.\nMarin was among those who attended the private auction for the &lt;a href=\"X-52%20Personnel%20Armor\"&gt;X-52 Personnel Armor&lt;/a&gt;. After Gallywix took &lt;a href=\"Hobart%20Grapplehammer\"&gt;Hobart Grapplehammer&lt;/a&gt; hostage to get the armor for himself, Marin joined the battle against Gallywix. After Hobart was freed and Gallywix beaten, the armor fell into the possession of &lt;a href=\"Goblin%20%28playable%29\"&gt;Gallywix's old rival&lt;/a&gt;.\nQuests.\nOnce his quest chain was completed, he would sell &lt;a href=\"Noggenfogger%20Elixir\"&gt;Noggenfogger Elixir&lt;/a&gt;s.\nQuotes.\nGadgetzan.\nWhen spoken to:\nWhen spoken to if the character has completed Marin's pre-&lt;a href=\"patch%204.0.3a\"&gt;patch 4.0.3a&lt;/a&gt; quests:\nDialogue with &lt;a href=\"Megs%20Dreadshredder\"&gt;Megs Dreadshredder&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=\"Kelsey%20Steelspark\"&gt;Kelsey Steelspark&lt;/a&gt;:\nClassic.\nLiving out there in the desert is rough! I get so thirsty standing outside in this heat.\nWell, now that you mention it, yeah, I did see something I thought was a little strange yesterday afternoon.\nI was running past some old troll ruins southeast of here; well, I wasn't really running, more like hopping... the sand's so hot!\nAnyway, so I was hopping past these ruins, when I noticed a camp set up there. Seems like a funny place to set up camp, if you ask me... I would have poked around a little more but one of those crazy big vultures chased me off."}
