{"id": "64828", "revid": "46586549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=64828", "title": "Violet Eye", "text": "The Violet Eye is a secret sect founded by the &lt;a href=\"Kirin%20Tor\"&gt;Kirin Tor&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt;, they were assigned to keep an eye on &lt;a href=\"Karazhan\"&gt;Karazhan&lt;/a&gt; and to spy on the &lt;a href=\"Guardian%20of%20Tirisfal\"&gt;Guardian of Tirisfal&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Medivh\"&gt;Medivh&lt;/a&gt; and his works. Although Medivh was dead for decades, and Karazhan somehow sealed itself off to the outside world, the Violet Eye remained to study the tower and the effects of its magic disturbances on &lt;a href=\"Deadwind%20Pass\"&gt;Deadwind Pass&lt;/a&gt;.\nAs Karazhan is a portal into &lt;a href=\"Twisting%20Nether\"&gt;Twisting Nether&lt;/a&gt;, a beacon shining into other worlds, it's the Violet Eye's mission to ensure that the tower don't fall into the wrong hands, or the possible repercussions would be unthinkable. When the tower reopened and &lt;a href=\"Prince%20Malchezaar\"&gt;Prince Malchezaar&lt;/a&gt; took control of it, the Violet Eye fought to regain control of Karazhan with the help of the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;s. Years later, they faced the Legion once more during the &lt;a href=\"Third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion&lt;/a&gt; of &lt;a href=\"Azeroth\"&gt;Azeroth&lt;/a&gt;, when &lt;a href=\"Viz%27aduum%20the%20Watcher\"&gt;Viz'aduum the Watcher&lt;/a&gt; was tasked by &lt;a href=\"Kil%27jaeden\"&gt;Kil'jaeden&lt;/a&gt; to use Karazhan as a conduit to every world consumed during the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Crusade\"&gt;Burning Crusade&lt;/a&gt;.\nThe heroes who provided aid and service received the &lt;a href=\"Violet%20Signet\"&gt;Violet Signet&lt;/a&gt;, a magical ring that grew in power as they continued to prove their worth and loyalty to the Violet Eye. The higher their reputation with the organization, the more &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Leryda\"&gt;Archmage Leryda&lt;/a&gt; released the power contained in the signet to reward them. And for those who exceeded the expectations of the mages, achieving the highest honor available to non-citizens of &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt;, the ring became as powerful as those of the archmages of the Kirin Tor and a symbol so that the initiated may recognize their allegiance.\nHistory.\nAmong the agent the Violet Eye sent to infiltrate Karazhan, &lt;a href=\"Koren\"&gt;Koren&lt;/a&gt; the &lt;a href=\"blacksmith\"&gt;blacksmith&lt;/a&gt; of the tower was under their pay. Though not a member of the Violet Eye, he pretended to serve Medivh and helped the Violet Eye to keep a close eye on the Guardian. The &lt;a href=\"spy\"&gt;spy&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Keanna\"&gt;Keanna&lt;/a&gt; was also present in the tower, where she was staying up at the guest chambers. After Medivh was killed, Karazhan sealed itself off to the outside world and the agents remained locked inside, while their allies outside never heard from any of them again. Inside, the agents died for unknown reasons, and the magic of the tower notably prevented Koren's soul from finding eternal rest.\nFor unknown reasons, &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; had many disagreements with &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Cedric\"&gt;Archmage Cedric&lt;/a&gt; in the past, but still considers that the work that men like &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Alturus\"&gt;Archmage Alturus&lt;/a&gt; do is important. On the field, Archmage Alturus is a high ranking member of the Violet Eye responsible for gathering information about the state of Karazhan, while his immediate supervisor is Archmage Cedric at &lt;a href=\"Dalaran%20Crater\"&gt;Dalaran Crater&lt;/a&gt;. At some point, Cedric assigned &lt;a href=\"Mage%20Darius\"&gt;Apprentice Darius&lt;/a&gt; to help Alturus in his tasks and research.\nThe Burning Crusade.\nAt some point after the reopening of the &lt;a href=\"Dark%20Portal\"&gt;Dark Portal&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Alturus\"&gt;Archmage Alturus&lt;/a&gt; sent &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Tasserel\"&gt;Apprentice Tasserel&lt;/a&gt; to &lt;a href=\"Shattrath%20City\"&gt;Shattrath City&lt;/a&gt; to look for assistance. While he was not allowed outside of &lt;a href=\"Lower%20City\"&gt;Lower City&lt;/a&gt;, he nevertheless managed to convince the &lt;a href=\"adventurer\"&gt;adventurer&lt;/a&gt;, and sent them to &lt;a href=\"Karazhan\"&gt;Karazhan&lt;/a&gt; to help the cause of the Violet Eye. In the meantime, he looked for a way to access the rest of the city after hearing the rumor that an &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;old associate&lt;/a&gt; of theirs was present somewhere.\nWhen the adventurer arrived, Archmage Alturus asked for their help to discover the reason for the ghosts around Karazhan, precisely some of their essences to study them. He also sent them with a scrying crystal to obtain an imprint of Karazhan's energy, and discovered that the haunted tower was no longer emanating all manner of arcane currents, but instead, became a huge energy vacuum with a very faint &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic echo. After it was reported to the organization, &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Cedric\"&gt;Archmage Cedric&lt;/a&gt; sent the adventurer to meet Khadgar in Shattrath, their \"old associate\", because he was the only one who could reopen Karazhan so that Violet Eye could act.\nWith the help of Khadgar, and somehow of Medivh in the past, the adventurers managed to reform &lt;a href=\"The%20Master%27s%20Key\"&gt;The Master's Key&lt;/a&gt;. Before they left, Khadgar told them to be careful that the Violet Eye didn't try to use them, for they were the ones with the key, but that if their investigations were true, then it would be important to help them. Once Karazhan was reopened, Archmage Alturus sent the adventurer to assess the situation inside and to find &lt;a href=\"Keanna%27s%20Log\"&gt;Keanna's Log&lt;/a&gt;, an encoded log of all her observations, and advised them to seek help from the ghost &lt;a href=\"Koren\"&gt;Koren&lt;/a&gt;. Once in possession of the log, they discovered that &lt;a href=\"Keanna\"&gt;Keanna&lt;/a&gt; had detected the arrival of a &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt; agent at the top of the tower before her death.\nFor all their help, the adventurer was rewarded by Archmage Alturus, as in his own words, gaining the favor of the archmages of &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; is not something one can regret. However, Archmage Cedric later explained that it wasn't over, as it was only a matter of time until the demons renewed their attacks while the Violet Eye stood powerless on the sidelines. The archmage then asked once more for the help of the adventurers to put an end to the plans of the Legion.\nIn the meantime, the Violet Eye sent three agents to track down &lt;a href=\"Medivh%27s%20Journal\"&gt;Medivh's Journal&lt;/a&gt;, but none of them came out and the adventurer was thus sent to accomplish the mission. Inside the tower, the agents &lt;a href=\"Wravien\"&gt;Wravien&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Gradav\"&gt;Gradav&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Kamsis\"&gt;Kamsis&lt;/a&gt;, somehow succumbed to the dark magic of Karazhan during their investigation, dooming their souls to relive their final moments forever. Despite the curse, they still managed to help the adventurer who later brought back the diary to Archmage Alturus.\nWith the information and memories inside, centered on the battle between Medivh and &lt;a href=\"Arcanagos\"&gt;Arcanagos&lt;/a&gt;, Archmage Alturus determined that this was an opportunity for them to retrieve some of the Guardian's magical essence from the blue dragon's remains. Once in possession of one of the bones, he sent the adventurer to meet &lt;a href=\"Kalynna%20Lathred\"&gt;Kalynna Lathred&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Netherstorm\"&gt;Netherstorm&lt;/a&gt;, a former member of the Kirin Tor in pursuit of knowledge forbidden, in order to raise the dragon back from the dead. With her help, the adventurers managed to resurrected Arcanagos as the &lt;a href=\"undead%20dragon\"&gt;undead dragon&lt;/a&gt; &lt;a href=\"Nightbane\"&gt;Nightbane&lt;/a&gt;, and after they defeated him, they brought the essence to Alturus, who announced that this would reveal vital information about Medivh.\nLegion.\nAt the time of the &lt;a href=\"third%20invasion%20of%20the%20Burning%20Legion\"&gt;third invasion of the Burning Legion&lt;/a&gt;, when the &lt;a href=\"Burning%20Legion\"&gt;Legion&lt;/a&gt; forces marched into &lt;a href=\"Karazhan\"&gt;Karazhan&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=\"Moroes\"&gt;Moroes&lt;/a&gt; saw this as a sign of &lt;a href=\"Medivh\"&gt;Medivh&lt;/a&gt;'s return and killed &lt;a href=\"Apprentice%20Darius\"&gt;Apprentice Darius&lt;/a&gt;. According to &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Alturus\"&gt;Archmage Alturus&lt;/a&gt;, the Legion's arrival was no surprise, as the power they coveted beneath the tower had already existed for a long time. Alturus and &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Leryda\"&gt;Archmage Leryda&lt;/a&gt;, alongside a few mages of the Kirin Tor, were later seen holding off the &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt;ic reinforcements from reaching the gates of the &lt;a href=\"Master%27s%20Cellar\"&gt;Master's Cellar&lt;/a&gt;. When the adventurer arrived, Leryda asked them to push the demons back, because if the Legion forces had continued to grow, the Violet Eye would not have been able to hold their ground.\nAfter his death, Darius became a &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt; and was granted the rank of mage posthumously. He then received the new charge of sprucing up the tower, in order for it to be a bit more inviting in case &lt;a href=\"Khadgar\"&gt;Archmage Khadgar&lt;/a&gt; had further need of it. Now able to enter the tower safely, Darius enlisted the help of the adventurers in his tasks to clear Karazhan of the vermin inside, to calm the &lt;a href=\"ghost\"&gt;ghost&lt;/a&gt;s in the &lt;a href=\"Opera%20Hall\"&gt;Opera Hall&lt;/a&gt;, and to disable &lt;a href=\"The%20Curator\"&gt;The Curator&lt;/a&gt; once more.\nWhen the heroes had to defeat &lt;a href=\"Nightbane%20%28Return%20to%20Karazhan%20tactics%29\"&gt;Nightbane&lt;/a&gt; over again, Darius remarked that Archmage Alturus' idea of \u200b\u200braising an &lt;a href=\"undead%20dragon\"&gt;undead dragon&lt;/a&gt; back to life, in order to study the Guardian's powers, hadn't been such a good idea on the long term.\nReputation.\nQuests.\nThere is a large and complex chain that has the player visit several dungeons of Outland in order for them to obtain &lt;a href=\"The%20Master%27s%20Key\"&gt;The Master's Key&lt;/a&gt;, which allows for entrance to Karazhan and beyond.\n\"10275 reputation total\"\nRewards.\nRings.\nAt reputation, &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Leryda\"&gt;Archmage Leryda&lt;/a&gt; at the entrance to &lt;a href=\"Karazhan\"&gt;Karazhan&lt;/a&gt; will offer players a quest to receive a ring. The rings are progressively upgraded as the player gains higher reputation.\nEach ring set is received as quest rewards. The quests all follow the same pattern, with the only distinction being the first quest's title.\nVendors.\nDarius is the traditional faction quartermaster.\nInside Karazhan, Koren the blacksmith offers a few recipes to players who are honored with the Violet Eye."}
