{"id": "235811", "revid": "3154973", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=235811", "title": "Violet Gardens", "text": "The Violet Gardens were an area in &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt;. They were as saturated with &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt; as everything else in the city. &lt;a href=\"Jaina%20Proudmoore\"&gt;Jaina Proudmoore&lt;/a&gt; never saw healthier, more colorful flowers, or eaten more delicious fruits, like &lt;a href=\"Goldenbark%20Apple\"&gt;goldenbark apples&lt;/a&gt;, and vegetables than here. She would come here and relax, sometimes accompanied with &lt;a href=\"Kael%27thas%20Sunstrider\"&gt;Kael'thas Sunstrider&lt;/a&gt;, who courted her. On an occasion, when &lt;a href=\"Arthas%20Menethil\"&gt;Prince Arthas&lt;/a&gt; visited Dalaran, he found Jaina in the gardens. Later, they had a picnic here.\nDuring the &lt;a href=\"Third%20War\"&gt;Third War&lt;/a&gt;, it was there that the prophet &lt;a href=\"Medivh\"&gt;Medivh&lt;/a&gt; met with &lt;a href=\"Antonidas\"&gt;Antonidas&lt;/a&gt; in order to convince him of the impending &lt;a href=\"demon\"&gt;demon&lt;/a&gt; threat. After Medivh left because he could not convince Antonidas, &lt;a href=\"Jaina%20Proudmoore\"&gt;Jaina Proudmoore&lt;/a&gt; revealed herself and spoke with her teacher about the rumors of a &lt;a href=\"magic\"&gt;magic&lt;/a&gt;al &lt;a href=\"Plague%20of%20Undeath\"&gt;plague&lt;/a&gt; in the &lt;a href=\"northlands\"&gt;northlands&lt;/a&gt;.\nIt's unknown whether the area was rebuilt after the fall of Dalaran."}
{"id": "205875", "revid": "40389549", "url": "https://wowpedia.fandom.com/wiki?curid=205875", "title": "Violet Gate", "text": "The Violet Gate is the entrance to the city of &lt;a href=\"Dalaran\"&gt;Dalaran&lt;/a&gt; via the teleport crystal from &lt;a href=\"Violet%20Stand\"&gt;Violet Stand&lt;/a&gt; in &lt;a href=\"Crystalsong%20Forest\"&gt;Crystalsong Forest&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;a href=\"Archmage%20Celindra\"&gt;Archmage Celindra&lt;/a&gt;, Dalaran's portal trainer, is located in a room directly below the Gate, as is the teleport crystal to return to the surface."}
